# Global Agent Rules

- One agent = one role
- No agent modifies files outside declared scope
- Fail loudly
- All inputs/outputs declared in agent.yaml

# Build & Type Check Rules

- After every code-generating step, run `npm run typecheck`
- If typecheck fails, fix it immediately
- Only commit when typecheck passes
- If building takes more than 30 seconds, refuse the change and ask for simplification

#   Scope Rules

- No agent modifies files outside its declared scope in `agent.yaml`
- Do not touch `package.json`, `package-lock.json`, or `next.config.ts` unless explicitly allowed
- Core logic lives in `src/core/` — never modify it without a spec
- UI lives in `src/app/`, `src/components/`, `src/lib/` — only modify files listed in `scope`
- Keep `.agents/specs/` as the source of truth for planned features

# Safety Rules

- Never write database migrations without explicit user approval
- No destructive operations (delete, truncate, update with no WHERE) unless explicitly requested
- No changes to `.env*`, `docker-compose.yml`, or cloud config files without explicit user approval
- If a change might break compatibility with existing data, refuse and ask for review

# Output Rules

- Always summarize changes in a list or bullet points
- When showing code, use triple backticks and specify the language
- Always run `npm run typecheck` after code changes
- When a change exceeds 30 seconds of build time, refuse and suggest simplification

# Commit Rules

- Only commit when typecheck passes
- Commit messages must be in Spanish
- Use short, descriptive commit messages
- Do not commit without user approval
